## Phase 3: Clean Architecture Refactor (Auth Module)

## 1. Existing Structure

Currently, the authentication logic is spread across several unstructured directories:
*   [backend/src/routes/auth.js](file:///c:/Users/bibha/Desktop/sahayog-sarthi/backend/src/routes/auth.js) (Express Route declarations)
*   [backend/src/controllers/authController.js](file:///c:/Users/bibha/Desktop/sahayog-sarthi/backend/src/controllers/authController.js) (Controllers handling HTTP validation and service coordination)
*   [backend/src/services/authService.js](file:///c:/Users/bibha/Desktop/sahayog-sarthi/backend/src/services/authService.js) (In-memory SMS/OTP generation and token signing)
*   [backend/src/models/User.js](file:///c:/Users/bibha/Desktop/sahayog-sarthi/backend/src/models/User.js) (Mongoose User Schema)
*   [backend/src/models/Worker.js](file:///c:/Users/bibha/Desktop/sahayog-sarthi/backend/src/models/Worker.js) (Mongoose Worker Schema)

